Rattatak is an Outer Rim world unknown to the Galactic Republic at the time of the Clone Wars. Rattatak is a dry, arid, mountainous planet covered in red rock, judging by its appearance from orbit. Most settlements appear to be hewn into the rock itself.

It was here that Count Dooku first discovered and recruited Asajj Ventress as he watched her emerge victorious at the gladiatorial death matches of The Cauldron. He introduced her to Darth Sidious who gave the dark side warrior her first assignment, which was to kill Anakin Skywalker. Later in the Clone Wars, Obi-Wan Kenobi was transported to Rattatak by Ventress after the Battle of Jabiim.

Bakura is a pastoral planet of the very edge of known space, just outside the Moddell Sector in the Outer Rim. It is the only inhabitable planet in the eight-planet system of the same name. Its terrain is comprised mostly of mountains, valleys, plains, and small seas, all of which receive a great deal of rain; Leia Organa views Bakura as being very similar to a wetter Alderaan. The capital city is Salis D'aar, which is between two of Bakura's major rivers. The Ssi-Ruuk call the planet Xwhee.

Endor (also known as the Forest Moon of Endor and the Sanctuary Moon) is a small forested moon orbiting the gas giant planet of Endor. An enchanted world, Endor is notable for being the native home of the Ewoks. Due to its proximity to the inhospitable Unknown Regions, Endor is a relatively quiet planetoid.

Lwhekk is the capital of the Ssi-ruuvi Imperium and is located beyond the main disk of the Galaxy, in the remote Ssi-ruuk Star Cluster.

Lwhekk is a humid, jungle-covered planet beyond the known Galaxy. The jungles of Lwhekk are broken by spired cities which appear to be quite fragile against the jungle. The planet also has volcanoes and a large part of it appears to be covered by oceans.

Cerea is a planet located in the Mid Rim region of the galaxy. The homeworld of the Cerean species, Cerea is notable for its inhabitants' harmonious relationship with nature. Technology and pollution are frowned upon by the conservative government, a major point in the planet's decision not to join the Galactic Republic. The Cerean population mainly live in giant buildings that took up a minimum of space, allowing the remainder of the planet's area to be employed as farmland. Foreign immigrants and visitors are, with a few exceptions, only allowed in Cerea's Outsider Citadels, enormous buildings erected to let non-Cereans practice their technological ways. This ensure that the foreigners' technology didn't contaminate Cerea's nature, but also led to a concentration of criminal elements within the Citadels.

Cerea is ruled by the Council of Elders, which in turn is led by a president. The planet is situated far away from any major hyperspace routes, and is for the most part ignored by the Republic until a few years prior to the Clone Wars. Cerea's seclusion caused a unique culture to develop, one that focused on other values than the mainstream galactic civilization. In 21 BBY, Cerea was the site of a battle between the Republic and Confederacy of Independent Systems, which had an adverse effect on the planet's relatively untouched nature.

Reytha is one of the most productive agriworlds of the Galactic Republic and its microclimates ensure that it has suitable growing conditions all year round. Genetic modifications like special synthesizers and genetic inducer-droids were introduced on a greater scale, and the planet has since become known as the 'breadbasket of the Empire', producing 10% of the food for the Imperial military. Its major crop is muja fruit; Reythan berries are also produced here. Reytha's seas and oceans are teeming with fish and are almost as productive as its agricultural fields.

Reytha's main settlement is the city of Yeere, which holds the only spaceport on the planet and is also garrisoned with a meager number of troops. During major conflicts, when agriworlds become prime targets, Yeere has been the location of reinforced fortresses and strongholds.

The large Montrosa Ocean keeps the planet cool and drives the bountiful rains that nourish the soil. The ocean is the location of an island chain popular with Mon Calamari star tours.
